# threeSecondRule3D (Godot 4.7)

First-person 3D driving game: get to work (10 miles) while practicing the **3-second following rule**. Main scene: `res://scenes/main.tscn`.

## Architecture

| Script | Role |
|--------|------|
| `scripts/game_manager.gd` | Win/lose, HUD updates, following-time display, restart on Enter |
| `scripts/player_vehicle.gd` | Speed, lane snap, movement along +Z, crash signal |
| `scripts/traffic_manager.gd` | Spawn/despawn NPC traffic, car-to-car spacing, player collision, `get_following_seconds()` |
| `scripts/traffic_car.gd` | NPC bus movement, loads/fits `assets/vw_bus.glb`, exposes `get_rear_z()` / `get_front_z()` |
| `scripts/road_manager.gd` | Recycled road segments |
| `scripts/dashboard_hud.gd` | In-cockpit LED displays (MPH, miles to work, follow seconds) |

Traffic scene: `scenes/traffic_car.tscn` (root + script only; model spawned at runtime).

## Controls (`project.godot` input actions)

- **Up / Down** — accelerate / decelerate (hold; ramps over time)
- **Space** — brake (hold; strong ramp)
- **A / D or Left / Right arrows** — snap to adjacent lane (not continuous strafe)

## Lane & coordinate conventions

- Road forward is **+Z**. Lanes at `x = -1.85` (left) and `x = 1.85` (right).
- Camera is X-flipped, so `lane_left` action sets `LANE_RIGHT_X` and `lane_right` sets `LANE_LEFT_X` in `player_vehicle.gd` — **do not swap back** without checking in-game feel.
- Lane changes use `move_toward` to `target_lane_x` on key press (`is_action_just_pressed`).

## Traffic & 3D assets

- NPC vehicle model: **`res://assets/vw_bus.glb`** (replaced earlier `vw_bus.fbx`). Prefer **glTF/GLB** for new vehicle assets.
- `traffic_car.gd` loads the GLB at runtime, scales to `TARGET_LENGTH` (4.5 m), centers on road, caches bumper offsets from mesh AABB.
- Default `model_rotation_degrees` is `Vector3.ZERO` (was 180° before orientation fix).
- `@export model_extra_scale` for manual tuning in the inspector.

### Sketchfab / vw_bus.glb caveats

- Export has **messy bounds** (e.g. huge internal dimensions, generic `Object_*` names, `steel2` / `Rubber_Rough222` materials). `_estimate_vehicle_length()` rejects outlier axes (`MAX_MESH_AXIS`, 8× ratio rule).
- **Do not use fixed `CAR_LENGTH` offsets** for gap math — use `_rear_z_offset` / `_front_z_offset` from fitted mesh bounds.
- **Wheel spin was attempted and removed.** Rims were separate meshes without proper hub pivots; spinning looked wrong. Do **not** re-add rim rotation unless a new model has dedicated wheel nodes/bones. User plans to source a better model.

### Traffic spacing & HUD following time

- Gaps measured **bumper to bumper**: `car.get_rear_z() - player.get_front_z()` (`get_front_z()` = player `z + 1.8`).
- `SPAWN_MIN_AHEAD = 60` (~3 s at cruise) aligns with game theme; `MIN_CAR_GAP = 10`, `LANE_SPAWN_SPACING = 22`.
- `_enforce_car_spacing()` slows cars that close on same-lane traffic.
- HUD follow seconds: green ≥ 3 s, yellow ≥ 1.5 s, red below; shows `--` when no car in lane (`≥ 90`).

## GDScript conventions (this project)

- Use **explicit `float` types** when inference fails, e.g. `var world_z: float = _lane_spawn_z[lane_x]` and `var gap: float = ...` on `Node3D` with script methods.
- Defer model fitting: `call_deferred("_fit_model_to_road", model)` after adding the GLB child.
- Keep traffic logic in `traffic_manager.gd`; avoid duplicating lane constants — they must stay in sync across `player_vehicle`, `traffic_manager`, and `traffic_car`.

## Editor / tooling

- **godot_ai** MCP plugin enabled (`addons/godot_ai/`). Large assets may need headless import: `Godot --headless --import --path <project>`.
- Do not commit secrets. Avoid editing `addons/godot_ai/` unless fixing the plugin itself.

## When changing vehicles

1. Drop GLB in `assets/`, let Godot import, update `BUS_MODEL_PATH` if filename changes.
2. Verify orientation via `model_rotation_degrees` (likely 0 or 180 on Y).
3. Re-check HUD follow time and collision gaps after any model swap — visual position must match `_cache_extent_offsets()`.
4. For animated wheels later: require separate wheel nodes with pivots at hub centers, or a rigged model.
